rmed by TypeScript and ESLint checks that passed without issue.\n\n\n**Validating Design Alignment**\n\nI've confirmed that the secure preview notice, integrated into `notices-avatars.tsx`, aligns perfectly with the decoupled architecture, simulating secure enclaves as intended. It looks like the design instructions are being followed.\n\n\n**Refining UI Interactivity**\n\nI'm now diving deeper into how to enhance the interactive feel of the private-app shell. I've reviewed the design of the \"ZERO-TRUST SANDBOX ENCLAVE\" section in `app-shell.tsx`, finding its styling and contextual information to be excellent. Now, I'm analyzing the mobile bottom navigation links, noting the dynamic role-based rendering of primary links within `app-shell.tsx`. The code is brilliant, providing a personalized and intuitive user experience.\n\n\n"}}
