ploads, payments, or real API calls were added. Verify no landing page files were changed. Run npm run lint, npm run build, npm run typecheck if available, and npm test if available. Final response must include pass/fail checklist, files changed, commands run, remaining warnings, and TODOs for Phase 5 backend.\"\n   },\n   {\n     \"id\": \"122-phase5-preflight-backend-mvp-audit\",\n@@ -853,7 +853,7 @@\n     \"scope\": \"phase5-backend-database\",\n     \"target\": \"database models\",\n     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n-    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP database models for the admin and client portal only. Do not create models for GFF AI tools such as Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, or Foundry Studio. Required models: User, ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, AnalyticsSnapshot or AnalyticsEvent, GovernanceItem, ActivityEvent, Notification. Use simple fields that support the Phase 4 UI. User fields: id, name, email, hashed_password, role, client_id nullable, status, created_at, updated_at. Roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, viewer. ClientAccount fields: id, name, industry, region, status, account_owner, created_at. Project fields: id, client_id, name, phase, status, health, owner, start_date, target_date, progress, description. AgentOperation fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, name, agent_type, status, health, owner, governance_status, last_activity_at. DocumentItem fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, document_type, status, version, owner, visibility, created_at. Invoice fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, invoice_number, status, amount, currency, due_date, issued_date. SupportTicket fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, category, priority, status, assigned_to, created_by, description, created_at. GovernanceItem fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, severity, status, owner, due_date, description. ActivityEvent and Notification should connect to module/entity where possible. Keep relationships simple. Run backend import check.\"\n+    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP database models for the admin and client portal only. Do not create models for GFF AI tools such as Blueprint, ROI, Proposal, Assessment, Sandbox, Marketplace, or Foundry Studio. Required models: User, ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem. Use simple fields that support the Phase 4 UI. User fields: id, name, email, hashed_password, role, client_id nullable, status, created_at, updated_at. Roles: client_admin, client_member, gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, viewer. ClientAccount fields: id, name, industry, region, status, account_owner, created_at. Project fields: id, client_id, name, phase, status, health, owner, start_date, target_date, progress, description. AgentOperation fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, name, agent_type, status, health, owner, governance_status, last_activity_at. DocumentItem fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, document_type, status, version, owner, visibility, created_at. Invoice fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, invoice_number, status, amount, currency, due_date, issued_date. SupportTicket fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, category, priority, status, assigned_to, created_by, description, created_at. GovernanceItem fields: id, client_id, project_id nullable, title, severity, status, owner, due_date, description. ActivityEvent and should connect to module/entity where possible. Keep relationships simple. Run backend import check.\"\n   },\n   {\n     \"id\": \"127-phase5-pydantic-schemas\",\n@@ -861,7 +861,7 @@\n     \"scope\": \"phase5-backend-schemas\",\n     \"target\": \"API schemas\",\n     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n-    \"prompt\": \"Create Pydantic schemas for all MVP backend models. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Include create, update, list/read response schemas where useful for User, ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem, ActivityEvent, Notification. Include Auth schemas: LoginRequest, TokenResponse, CurrentUserResponse. Keep schemas simple. Use from_attributes or ORM mode depending on Pydantic version. Ensure schemas do not expose hashed_password. Keep response fields aligned with the Phase 4 frontend data needs. Run backend import check.\"\n+    \"prompt\": \"Create Pydantic schemas for all MVP backend models. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Include create, update, list/read response schemas where useful for User, ClientAccount, Project, AgentOperation, DocumentItem, Invoice, SupportTicket, GovernanceItem, Notification. Include Auth schemas: LoginRequest, TokenResponse, CurrentUserResponse. Keep schemas simple. Use from_attributes or ORM mode depending on Pydantic version. Ensure schemas do not expose hashed_password. Keep response fields aligned with the Phase 4 frontend data needs. Run backend import check.\"\n   },\n   {\n     \"id\": \"128-phase5-password-hashing-and-jwt-security\",\n@@ -893,7 +893,7 @@\n     \"scope\": \"phase5-backend-data\",\n     \"target\": \"seed data\",\n     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n-    \"prompt\": \"Create a safe local seed script for MVP backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Seed representative data only. Create dev users for roles: gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, client_admin, client_member, viewer. Use simple documented local passwords such as password123 only in dev seed documentation. Create 2 to 3 representative client accounts, several projects, agent operations, documents metadata, invoices, support tickets, governance items, activity events, and notifications. Do not use real client names or fake logos. Ensure seed script can be run repeatedly without duplicating data, either by checking existing emails/records or resetting safely with explicit command. Add README instructions. Run seed if safe and verify backend can start.\"\n+    \"prompt\": \"Create a safe local seed script for MVP backend. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Seed representative data only. Create dev users for roles: gff_admin, gff_operator, finance_admin, support_agent, client_admin, client_member, viewer. Use simple documented local passwords such as password123 only in dev seed documentation. Create 2 to 3 representative client accounts, several projects, agent operations, documents metadata, invoices, support tickets, governance items. Do not use real client names or fake logos. Ensure seed script can be run repeatedly without duplicating data, either by checking existing emails/records or resetting safely with explicit command. Add README instructions. Run seed if safe and verify backend can start.\"\n   },\n   {\n     \"id\": \"132-phase5-backend-run-scripts\",\n@@ -973,7 +973,7 @@\n     \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n     \"target\": \"dashboard APIs\",\n     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n-    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP dashboard summary APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/dashboard/client for client portal summary and GET /api/v1/dashboard/admin for admin summary. Client dashboard should return counts and recent records for that user's client_id: active projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, open support tickets, governance items, activity, notifications. Admin dashboard should return global counts and recent records across clients: clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance, users, activity. Values must come from local database records, not hardcoded frontend mock data. Keep queries simple. Run backend checks.\"\n+    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP dashboard summary APIs. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/dashboard/client for client portal summary and GET /api/v1/dashboard/admin for admin summary. Client dashboard should return counts and recent records for that user's client_id: active projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, open support tickets, governance items. Admin dashboard should return global counts and recent records across clients: clients, projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support, governance, users, activity. Values must come from local database records, not hardcoded frontend mock data. Keep queries simple. Run backend checks.\"\n   },\n   {\n     \"id\": \"144-phase5-api-analytics-summary\",\n@@ -981,7 +981,7 @@\n     \"scope\": \"phase5-portal-admin-api\",\n     \"target\": \"analytics APIs\",\n     \"allowLandingChanges\": false,\n-    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP analytics APIs under /api/v1/analytics. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/analytics/client and GET /api/v1/analytics/admin. Use database aggregation from projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, governance items, and activity events. Keep it simple: counts by status, counts by phase, support by priority, invoice by status, AI operations by health, governance by severity. No fake live analytics. No external analytics provider. Client roles see only their client_id data. Admin roles see all. Run backend checks.\"\n+    \"prompt\": \"Create MVP analytics APIs under /api/v1/analytics. Do not touch landing page or GFF AI tools. Endpoints: GET /api/v1/analytics/client and GET /api/v1/analytics/admin. Use database aggregation from projects, AI operations, documents, invoices, support tickets, governance items. Keep it simple: counts by status, counts by phase, support by priority, invoice by status, AI operations by health, governance by severity. No fake live analytics. No external analytics provider. Client roles see only their client_id data. Admin roles see all. Run backend checks.\"\n   },\n   {\n     \"id\": \"145-phase5-backend-error-handling-and-pagination\",\n","success":true}],"durationMs":42}}
